== Events == * In the 1st year of the Chōkyū era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1040]] {{ill|December 16|ja|12月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – the era name was changed to Chōkyū from Chōryaku. * In the 2nd year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1869]] {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – a construction plan was decided for three railway branches: the main line connecting Tokyo and Kyoto, a line from Tokyo to Yokohama, another from Kyoto to Kobe, and a branch along Lake Biwa to Tsuruga.
== Births == * In the 12th year of the Tenpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1841]] {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Saitō Kichi (also known as Tangren Okichi), a samurai serving under Consul General {{ill|Townsend Harris|ja|Townsend Harris|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in Japan (died [[1890]]).
== Deaths == * In the 9th year of the Genroku era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1696]] {{ill|December 4|ja|12月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor Meishō, the 109th Emperor of Japan (born [[1623]]).
