{{Not to be confused with|November 10|qq=November 10}}<!--hatnote--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月初十|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 10일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 10''' is the 10th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}, and the day is designated as {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=}}.
== Events == * In the 1st year of the Chōkyū era ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1040]] [[:en:December 16|December 16]]) – the era name was changed to Chōkyū from Chōryaku. * In the 2nd year of the Meiji era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1869]] [[:en:December 12|December 12]]) – a construction plan was decided for three railway branches: the main line connecting Tokyo and Kyoto, a line from Tokyo to Yokohama, another from Kyoto to Kobe, and a branch along Lake Biwa to Tsuruga.
== Births == * In the 12th year of the Tenpō era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1841]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]]) – Saitō Kichi (also known as Tangren Okichi), a samurai serving under Consul General {{ill|Townsend Harris|ja|Townsend Harris|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Townsend Harris|qq=}} in Japan (died [[1890]]).
== Deaths == * In the 9th year of the Genroku era ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1696]] [[:en:December 4|December 4]]) – Emperor Meishō, the 109th Emperor of Japan (born [[1623]]).
