'''November 10''' is the 10th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}, and the day is designated as {{ill|Tomobiki|WD=Q96759840|1=tomobiki}}{{efn|ja|友引|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* In the 1st year of the Chōkyū era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1040|en|1040|WD=Q19342|lt=1040|1=1040}} {{ill|December 16|en|December 16|WD=Q2410|lt=December 16|1=December 16}}) – the era name was changed to Chōkyū from Chōryaku.
* In the 2nd year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1869|en|1869|WD=Q7720|lt=1869|1=1869}} {{ill|December 12|en|December 12|WD=Q2369|lt=December 12|1=December 12}}) – a construction plan was decided for three railway branches: the main line connecting Tokyo and Kyoto, a line from Tokyo to Yokohama, another from Kyoto to Kobe, and a branch along Lake Biwa to Tsuruga.

== Births ==
* In the 12th year of the Tenpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1841|en|1841|WD=Q7622|lt=1841|1=1841}} {{ill|December 22|en|December 22|WD=Q2636|lt=December 22|1=December 22}}) – Saitō Kichi (also known as Tangren Okichi), a samurai serving under Consul General {{ill|Townsend Harris|1=Townsend Harris|2=ja|3=タウンゼント・ハリス|ja|Townsend Harris|1=Townsend Harris|2=ja|3=タウンゼント・ハリス|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Townsend Harris|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q610626}} in Japan (died {{ill|1890|en|1890|WD=Q7832|lt=1890|1=1890}}).

== Deaths ==
* In the 9th year of the Genroku era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1696|en|1696|WD=Q7699|lt=1696|1=1696}} {{ill|December 4|en|December 4|WD=Q2310|lt=December 4|1=December 4}}) – Emperor Meishō, the 109th Emperor of Japan (born {{ill|1623|en|1623|WD=Q6818|lt=1623|1=1623}}).

